1)A train travels 60 miles in the first hour and then increases its speed by 10 miles per hour every hour. How long will it take for the train to cover a total distance of 300 miles?
2)There are five apples in a basket. You take three apples out of the basket. How many apples do you have now?
3)If a person saves $200 every month, how much money will they have saved in 2 years if they earn 5% interest annually on the total amount saved at the end of each year?(compounding).
4)A clock shows the time as 3:15. What is the angle between the hour hand and the minute hand?
5)A rectangular garden has a length that is twice its width. If the perimeter of the garden is 60 meters, what are the dimensions of the garden?
6)A man is looking at a picture of someone. His friend asks who it is, and the man replies, "Brothers and sisters, I have none. But that person's father is my father's son." Who is the person in the picture?
7)A company sells a product for $150. The cost to produce the product is $90. The company also has a fixed monthly cost of $3,000. How many products must the company sell in a month to break even?
8)In a certain city, 60% of the population are men, and 40% are women. If 30% of the men and 50% of the women are married, what percentage of the total population is married?
9)A man walks 5 miles south, then 5 miles east, and finally 5 miles north. How far is he from his starting point?
10)A box contains 5 red balls, 3 green balls, and 2 blue balls. If a ball is randomly picked from the box, what is the probability that the ball is either red or green?
11)If a rectangular room is 12 feet long and 8 feet wide, what is the area of the room in square feet?
12)If the sum of three consecutive integers is 75, what is the middle integer?.
13)A man is facing north. He turns 90 degrees to his left, then turns 180 degrees to his right. Which direction is he facing now?
14)A recipe requires 3 cups of flour for every 2 cups of sugar. If you have 12 cups of flour, how many cups of sugar are needed?
15)A boat travels 60 miles upstream in 4 hours and 60 miles downstream in 2 hours. What is the speed of the current?